description:
15 april 2020, the Commission, in cooperation with the President of the European Council, has put forward a European roadmap to phase-out the containment measures due to the coronavirus outbreak. The Commission's roadmap lists concrete recommendations Member States should consider when planning to lift containment measures: Gatherings of people should be progressively permitted, taking into account the specificities of different categories of activity, such as:
Schools and universities;
Commercial activity (retail) with possible gradation;
Social activity measures (restaurants, cafes) with possible gradation;
Mass gatherings
